  "cross_reference_notes": "## Executive Summary: Naresh Chandra Uttam Patel\n\n### Overall Assessment\nNaresh Chandra Uttam Patel (Samajwadi Party) represents Fatehpur, Uttar Pradesh. The current composite transparency score is 46.5/100 with low overall data confidence. Naresh Chandra Uttam Patel has a below-average transparency score of 46.5/100, indicating significant room for improvement. No criminal cases declared. High parliament attendance. Limited participation in parliamentary proceedings.\n\n### Fund Utilization & Development\nConstituency-level MPLADS figures for the 18th Lok Sabha are not published in a consistently accessible machine-readable source at this time. The legacy MoSPI/data.gov.in dataset covers older Lok Sabha terms and the eSAKSHI portal is treated as unavailable unless a per-constituency record is positively matched. This profile therefore marks MPLADS as unavailable rather than estimating fund amounts. Use the RTI template below for constituency-level verification.\n\n### Financial Transparency\nThe available financial record reports declared assets of Rs 4.93 crore; liabilities of Rs 0; net worth of Rs 4.93 crore. Asset fields are based on available open affidavit/declared data and should be interpreted with the stated source confidence of high.\n\n### Legal & Criminal Standing\nNo criminal cases are declared in the available affidavit-derived data. Criminal-record confidence is high.\n\n### Parliamentary Performance\nParliamentary activity currently records attendance at 90.0%, 0 questions, 3 debates and 0 private member bill(s). Committee membership data is not available or shows no committee assignment in the current cache. Legislative record fields show 0 bills introduced, 0 zero-hour mention(s) and 0 special mention(s), with unavailable source confidence.\n\n### Public Engagement & Accessibility\nPublic accessibility data has low confidence: 0 tracked social platform(s), 0 aggregate followers, and 10 recent/news-cache article(s) (0 positive, 0 negative, 10 neutral). Informational compensation data records total monthly compensation/allowances of Rs 2.45 lakh.\n\n### Data Quality & Caveats\nValidation recorded 1 warning(s) and 0 error-level flag(s). Low-confidence dimensions: mplads. State/national CAG context includes 8 MPLADS-related audit finding(s), used as context rather than direct proof against the MP. Missing or unavailable open-data fields are displayed explicitly rather than filled with estimates.\n\n### Key Takeaway\nNaresh Chandra Uttam Patel's profile is complete in the sense that every major dashboard section now has either data-backed values or an explicit availability caveat. The most important follow-up for this profile is to verify constituency-level MPLADS releases and expenditure through official RTI/departmental records because the public machine-readable sources are currently incomplete for the 18th Lok Sabha.",
